1.title: Episode #1.1
1.plot: When rapper G-Spot "mistakenly" exposes himself on Twitter, Jess (Bethany Watson) has to get the situation under control while Mike is on his way from the airport. Meanwhile, Ben (Ignacyo Matynia) is working with young pop phenomenon Jackie Starr (Kristen Vaganos) in the studio while her best friend/manager Diane (Kelsea Baker) tries to keep herself from a meltdown.

2.title: Episode #1.2
2.plot: East Pacific Records President, Amy (Lori Sommer), is on a rampage after some projects begin to go off the rails. Jackie Starr (Kristen Vaganos) is brought in to discuss album art, which Jess (Bethany Watson) and Ellie (Palmyra Mattner) feel might be a little bit much for her younger fan base. Meanwhile, Paul (Bry Poole) has to get Chill Cosby off some venue blacklists before his big comeback. Also starring Kelsea Baker, Robert Lee Leng, Jerica Young and a special guest appearance by recording artist Anya Marina.

3.title: Episode #1.3
3.plot: Jess (Bethany Watson), Jackie Starr (Kristen Vaganos) and Diane (Kelsea Baker) take a tour of Jackie's hometown venue ahead of her tour. Meanwhile, Morgan (Alsion Klemp) and crew have to deal with a blacked-out Beatzarat (Nate Fridson) and Ellie (Palymra Mattner) has her mid-year review with VP of Marketing, Tim (J-L Cauvin). Also starring Shawn Mathis Gooden, Jerica Young, Jason Taylor and Danielle Kirshenblat.

4.title: Episode #1.4
4.plot: Jackie (Kristen Vaganos) is doing radio for her upcoming tour which means Ellie (Palmyra Mattner) is on babysitting patrol. Jess (Bethany Watson) is dealing with Brian Ripps' new musical direction while Diane (Kelsea Baker) is having major Jackie withdrawal in her new role as Jess's assistant. While the interns are in the middle of a release party-planning disaster, Kirby (Jerica Young) and Tiana (Shawn Mathis Gooden) are in the middle of a disaster known as See You Next Tuesday. Also starring Shelley Rome, Caitlin Charles and Kyler Coburn.

6.title: Episode #1.6
6.plot: IT'S SHOW TIME. Jackie (Kristen Vaganos) is freaking out right before she hits the stage for the first show of her tour and it's up to Jess (Bethany Watson), Ellie (Palmyra Mattner) and the rest of the East Pacific crew to make sure the show goes on. Also starring Kelsea Baker, Lori Sommer, Jerica Young, Robert Lee Leng and Daemar Wright.
